{"title":"Gallery: The Tour’s double ascent of the mythical Mont Ventoux","link":"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/07/gallery-the-tours-double-ascent-of-the-mythical-mont-ventoux/","date":1625708454000,"content":"<div><div><p><a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/author/mattdeneefeditor/\"><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Gat5TmE_400x400-aspect-ratio-75-75.png\"></a></p></div><div><p>It was the most-anticipated stage of this year’s <a href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/tag/tour-de-france\" target=\"_blank\">Tour de France</a> with two ascents of the legendary Mont Ventoux. Stage 11 delivered a legendary performance from all-rounder extraordinaire Wout van Aert (Jumbo-Visma) who dropped a handful of climbers on the second ascent of Ventoux and soloed away to what Van Aert himself described as “maybe … my best victory ever”.</p><p>There was movement in the GC battle too. Tadej Pogačar (UAE Team Emirates) looked vulnerable for the first time, Jonas Vingegaard (Jumbo-Visma) showed great climbing form, and Ben O’Connor (AG2R Citröen) dropped time to slide from second to fifth.</p><p>As the riders leave Mont Ventoux behind, join us as we relive the action atop the ‘Giant of Provence’ courtesy of photographers Jered and Ashley Gruber, and Kristof Ramon.</p><figure><ul><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-1-1340x894.jpg\"><figcaption>Scene: Mont Ventoux, one of the Tour’s most legendary climbs.</figcaption></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-kramon-2-1340x894.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-3-1340x987.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-6-1340x894.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-kramon-8-1340x894.jpg\"><figcaption>Among those in the early breakaway: Van Aert and world champ Julian Alaphilippe (Deceuninck-QuickStep).</figcaption></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-5-1340x1207.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-8-1340x894.jpg\"><figcaption>One ascent done, one to go.</figcaption></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-7-1340x1125.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-10-1340x1072.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-kramon-9-1340x894.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-12-1340x564.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-11-1340x900.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-13-1340x1052.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-kramon-6-1340x894.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-kramon-7-1340x865.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-15-1340x1072.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-16-1340x894.jpg\"><figcaption>Chris Froome’s had some memorable days on Mont Ventoux. Stage 11 of the 2021 Tour was not one of them. The four-time Tour winner finished the stage more than half an hour down and now sits 142nd overall from 156 remaining riders.</figcaption></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-17-1340x894.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-20-1340x894.jpg\"><figcaption>Two times Ventoux meant a tough battle against the time cut for sprinters like Mark Cavendish (Deceuninck-QuickStep).</figcaption></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-21-1340x894.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-kramon-14-1340x894.jpg\"><figcaption>By the time Van Aert reached the moonscape of Ventoux’s summit for a second time, he was all alone, having attacked from the break.</figcaption></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-23-1340x894.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-31-1340x1005.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-kramon-15-1340x894.jpg\"><figcaption>The Trek-Segafredo duo of Bauke Mollema and Kenny Elissonde would go on to finish second and third on the stage, behind Van Aert.</figcaption></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-25-1340x894.jpg\"><figcaption>Vingegaard attacked from the group of GC favourites …</figcaption></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-26-1340x894.jpg\"><figcaption>… putting Pogačar in difficulty for the first time this Tour.</figcaption></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-27-1340x894.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-kramon-16-1340x894.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-29-1340x894.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-32-1340x1038.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-kramon-11-1340x871.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-33-1340x1121.jpg\"><figcaption>It’s been a while since we’ve seen Pogačar in difficulty like this. What it means for the rest of the Tour is anyone’s guess.</figcaption></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-28-1340x1011.jpg\"><figcaption>With O’Connor sliding down the GC, Rigo Uran (EF Education-Nippo – left) and Richard Carapaz (Ineos Grenadiers) were both able to move up a spot on the day, to second and fourth respectively.</figcaption></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-kramon-10-1340x894.jpg\"><figcaption>Van Aert descending to his fourth Tour stage win and perhaps the most amazing victory of his highly decorated career.</figcaption></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-kramon-12-1340x894.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-35-1340x1196.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-37-1340x894.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-kramon-18-1340x894.jpg\"></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-38-1340x894.jpg\"><figcaption>Cavendish ended up beating the time cut by roughly seven minutes and will have a shot at even more stage wins in the 10 days ahead.</figcaption></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-39-1340x894.jpg\"><figcaption>Luke Rowe (Ineos Grenadiers) finished on the other side of the time cut. The Welshman’s Tour is now over.</figcaption></figure></li><li><figure><img src=\"https://cdn-ctstaging.pressidium.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2021-tour-de-france-stage-11-ventoux-22-1340x894.jpg\"><figcaption>Victor Campenaerts’ Tour ended after the first ascent of Mont Ventoux. Ventoux was the first mountain the Qhubeka-NextHash rider ever climbed on a bike, aged 14, with his dad.<em> </em>“I wanted to continue to at least do Ventoux once to ensure I saw my dad,” he said. “It was a nice moment to see him there at the top and then it was quite clear that the time cut was not realistic so we had an opportunity to stop and spend a moment together.”</figcaption></figure></li></ul></figure></div></div>","author":"Matt de Neef","siteTitle":"CyclingTips","siteHash":"30feca30fb3902119bf2da6559e7337232527b61c9abe0a00f5d7543c6aa6c84","entryHash":"d7c51a6e4b94ffc490ff492a5e4337801f5f0a77fca6c9a1c637a4c9c0cbb6e8","category":"Cycling"}